</p></td></tr><tr><td valign="bottom"><a href="http://rx4rdf.sf.net"><img width="100" style="padding: 0px" height="33" alt="Powered by Rhizome" src="rhizome.gif"></a></td></tr></table></td><td cellpadding="0" width="75%" padding="0" cellspacing="0" id="contentTableCell"><table width="100%" id="contentTable" height="100%"><tr><td valign="top" id="titlebar" height="1">Download</td></tr><tr><td id="maincontent" valign="top"><p>Rx4RDF requires Python 2.2 or later and <a href="http://4suite.org/?xslt=downloadproduct.xslt&show=http%3A//4suite.org/data/software/4Suite">4Suite 1.0a1</a>. On Windows, <a href="http://www.python.org/windows/win32all">Win32 Extensions</a> must be installed or locking will be disabled.
</p><p><a href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=85676">Source (zip)</a>
</p><p><a href="http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=85676">Source (tar.gz)</a>
</p><h1>Install
</h1><p>This is a standard Python source distribution. To install:
<ol><li> Unzip
</li><li> Run <tt>python &lt;unzip dir>/setup.py install</tt>
</li></ol></p><h1>Quick Start
</h1><p>Once you've installed Rx4RDF, use this guide to quickly start playing with its various components:
</p><h2>RxPath
</h2><p>To run a query on an RDF or NTriples file:
</p><p><tt>python RDFDom.py myrdf.rdf [RxPath expression]
</tt></p><p>If [RxPath expression] is omitted it will start in interactive mode.
</p><h2>Racoon and Rhizome
</h2><p>Run a local copy of this site:
</p><ol><li><tt>cd &lt;unzip dir>/site
</tt></li><li><tt>python ../rx/racoon.py -a site-config.py
</tt></li><li>Browse to <a href="http://localhost:8000">http://localhost:8000</a> (edit server.cfg to change the port).
</li></ol><p>To start a fresh Rhizome site, just run Rhizome from the directory where you want the site to live:
</p><ol><li><tt>cd &lt;directory of the new site>
</tt></li><li><tt>python /&lt;rx4rdf root>/rx/racoon.py -a /&lt;rx4rdf root>/rhizome/rhizome-config.py
</tt></li></ol><h2>RxSLT, RxUpdate, RhizML
</h2><p>To experiment with RxSLT, RxUpdate, or RhizML run an instance of Rhizome and create or edit pages with this format.  Or see RDFDom.py or rhizml.py for programmatic interfaces.
</p><h2>RhizML
</h2><p>Convert RhizML to XML:
</p><p><tt>python rhizml.py [-p] [-d] [-m MyMarkupMapFactory()] rhizmlsample.rz.txt 
</tt></p><p>Options: 
<dl><dd>-p pretty print
</dd><dd>-d debug output
</dd><dd>-m [string that evaluates to an object compatible with rx.rhizml.DefaultMarkupMapFactory]
</dd></dl></p><h2>RxML
</h2><p>Convert a RDF or NTriples file to RxML/RhizML:
</p><p><tt>python rxml.py -r myrdf.rdf
</tt></p><p>Convert a RxML/XML file to RDF (NTriples):
</p><p><tt>python rxml.py -n myrdf.rdf
</tt></p></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" id="footer" colspan="2"></td></tr></table><!--(c) 2003-4 by Adam Souzis (asouzis@users.sourceforge.net) All rights reserved--></body></html>